message: Focus on using 'scissors' on 'soft' ingredients first; this reliably creates items worth 25. Avoid cutting 'hard' items, as this often results in negative value. Once you have a 'cut' item with positive value, use the 'frame' tool on it to increase its value by 20. For example, cutting an 'artificial, soft' item (like newspaper) gives 25, then framing it gives 45. The highest scores (70) were achieved by combining two 'soft' ingredients first (e.g., leaf and feather, or cardboard and ribbon), then cutting the *combined* item (which gives 50), and finally framing it (which brings it to 70). Be careful not to overmix ingredients as this can lead to very low values.
